      "content": "idk, some people say the mining for those minerals is actually really destructive to ecosystems and uses a ton of water and energy. if the \"clean\" energy requires a bunch of environmental damage just to build the stuff, isn't it still a bit of a trade-off? does that change how \"superior\" it is?",
